<subSubSection id="CEA5C5B3FF8DFF8AFCCCFF71FB8DFC21" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="86009638FF8DFF8AFCCCFF71FB8DFC21" blockId="13.[814,1454,194,921]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFCCCFF71FC0DFF62" bold="true" box="[814,941,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Remarks. –</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFC55FF71FBE3FF61" author="Sakai, T" box="[951,1091,194,217]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref16325" refString="Sakai, T., 1935. New or rare species of Brachyura, collected by the Misago during the zoological survey around the Izu Peninsula. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, 2 (32): 63 - 88, Pls. 6 - 8." type="journal article" year="1935">Sakai (1935)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFB5EFF71FA0DFF61" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" box="[1212,1453,194,217]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFB5EFF71FA0DFF61" box="[1212,1453,194,217]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporus orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="FEA8D6A8FF8DFF8AFC88FF51FC09FF41" box="[874,937,226,249]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Japan</collectingCountry>
, making it at that time, only the second species of the genus to be described and the first to be discovered in the Indo-Pacific. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFB95FE91FA09FE81" authority="Stimpson, 1871" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[1143,1449,290,313]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFB95FE91FB58FE81" box="[1143,1272,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFB1DFE91FA09FE81" author="Stimpson, W" box="[1279,1449,290,313]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="109 - 160" refId="ref16623" refString="Stimpson, W., 1871. Preliminary report on the Crustacea dredged in the Gulf Stream in the Straits of Florida, by L. F. de Pourtales, assistant United States Coast Survey. Part I. Brachyura. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard, 2 (2): 109 - 160." type="journal article" year="1871">Stimpson, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was originally established for one western Atlantic species, 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFCCCFED1FBD6FEC1" authority="Stimpson, 1871" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[814,1142,354,377]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papulosus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFCCCFED1FC1DFEC1" box="[814,957,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. papulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFC25FED1FBD6FEC1" author="Stimpson, W" box="[967,1142,354,377]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="109 - 160" refId="ref16623" refString="Stimpson, W., 1871. Preliminary report on the Crustacea dredged in the Gulf Stream in the Straits of Florida, by L. F. de Pourtales, assistant United States Coast Survey. Part I. Brachyura. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard, 2 (2): 109 - 160." type="journal article" year="1871">Stimpson, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFB66FED1FA9CFEC1" author="Zarenkov, N" box="[1156,1340,354,377]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref16833" refString="Zarenkov, N. A., 1971. On the species composition and ecology of the Decapoda in the Red Sea. In: Vodyanitzkii, V. A. (ed.) Benthos of the Continental Shelf of the Red Sea. Naukova Dumka, Kiev. pp. 155 - 203, Figs. 63 - 68 (in Russian)." type="book chapter" year="1971">Zarenkov (1971)</bibRefCitation>
described a third species, 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC0AFE31FBCEFE21" authorityName="Zarenkov" authorityYear="1971" box="[1000,1134,386,409]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guinotae">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC0AFE31FBCEFE21" box="[1000,1134,386,409]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. guinotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Red Sea and the western Indian Ocean. 
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFBDEFE11FB40FE01" author="Serene, R" box="[1084,1248,418,441]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref16482" refString="Serene, R., 1984. Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de l'ocean Indien occidental et de la mer Rouge. Xanthoidea: Xanthidae et Trapeziidae. Avec un addendum par A. Crosnier: Carpilidae et Menippidae. Faune tropicale, 24: 1 - 400, Pls. 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1984">Serène (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, citing comments made by 
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFC72FE71FB77FE61" author="Guinot-Dumortier, D" box="[912,1239,450,473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="153 - 218" refId="ref14960" refString="Guinot-Dumortier, D., 1960. Revision des genres Euxanthus Dana et Hypocolpus Rathbun (Crust. Decap. Brach.). Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 20 (2): 153 - 218, Pls. 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1960">Guinot-Dumortier (1960: 161)</bibRefCitation>
that there are many carapace, third maxilliped and chela characters distinguishing the Japanese species from the Atlantic one, established the genus 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC98FD91FBACFD81" authorityName="Serene" authorityYear="1984" box="[890,1036,546,569]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC98FD91FBACFD81" box="[890,1036,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Hepatoporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate both 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFAFEFD91FC0BFDE1" authority="Sakai, 1935" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFAFEFD91FA0EFD81" box="[1308,1454,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. orientalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFCCCFDF1FC0BFDE1" author="Sakai, T" box="[814,939,578,601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref16325" refString="Sakai, T., 1935. New or rare species of Brachyura, collected by the Misago during the zoological survey around the Izu Peninsula. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, 2 (32): 63 - 88, Pls. 6 - 8." type="journal article" year="1935">Sakai, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC3DFDF1FAADFDE1" authority="Zarenkov, 1971" authorityName="Zarenkov" authorityYear="1971" box="[991,1293,578,601]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guinotae">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC3DFDF1FBFBFDE1" box="[991,1115,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. guinotae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFB83FDF1FAADFDE1" author="Zarenkov, N" box="[1121,1293,578,601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref16833" refString="Zarenkov, N. A., 1971. On the species composition and ecology of the Decapoda in the Red Sea. In: Vodyanitzkii, V. A. (ed.) Benthos of the Continental Shelf of the Red Sea. Naukova Dumka, Kiev. pp. 155 - 203, Figs. 63 - 68 (in Russian)." type="book chapter" year="1971">Zarenkov, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFAF5FDF1FA0DFDE1" author="Serene, R" box="[1303,1453,578,601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref16482" refString="Serene, R., 1984. Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de l'ocean Indien occidental et de la mer Rouge. Xanthoidea: Xanthidae et Trapeziidae. Avec un addendum par A. Crosnier: Carpilidae et Menippidae. Faune tropicale, 24: 1 - 400, Pls. 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1984">Serène (1984)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC4FFDD1FB67FDC1" authority="Sakai, 1935" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" box="[941,1223,610,633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC4FFDD1FB99FDC1" box="[941,1081,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. orientalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFBA1FDD1FB67FDC1" author="Sakai, T" box="[1091,1223,610,633]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref16325" refString="Sakai, T., 1935. New or rare species of Brachyura, collected by the Misago during the zoological survey around the Izu Peninsula. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, 2 (32): 63 - 88, Pls. 6 - 8." type="journal article" year="1935">Sakai, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="5904289AFF8DFF8AFAFCFDD1FAEDFDC1" box="[1310,1357,610,633]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">type</typeStatus>
species. Takeda &amp; Nagai (1986) independently established a new genus, 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC95FD11FBB6FD01" authorityName="Takeda &amp; Nagai" authorityYear="1986" box="[887,1046,674,697]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC95FD11FBB6FD01" box="[887,1046,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to accomodate 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFB5CFD11FAE0FD01" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" box="[1214,1344,674,697]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFB5CFD11FAE0FD01" box="[1214,1344,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a new Japanese species they described, 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFB73FD71FAB7FD61" baseAuthorityName="Takeda &amp; Nagai" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[1169,1303,706,729]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinctus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFB73FD71FAB7FD61" box="[1169,1303,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. distinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species are known only from 
<collectingCountry id="FEA8D6A8FF8DFF8AFBC7FD51FBC6FD41" box="[1061,1126,738,761]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Takeda (1986) subsequently recognized 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC4CFCB1FB78FCA1" authority="Serene, 1984" authorityName="Serene" authorityYear="1984" box="[942,1240,770,793]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC4CFCB1FB9BFCA1" box="[942,1083,770,793]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Hepatoporus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E22EEBC9FF8DFF8AFBA4FCB1FB78FCA1" author="Serene, R" box="[1094,1240,770,793]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref16482" refString="Serene, R., 1984. Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de l'ocean Indien occidental et de la mer Rouge. Xanthoidea: Xanthidae et Trapeziidae. Avec un addendum par A. Crosnier: Carpilidae et Menippidae. Faune tropicale, 24: 1 - 400, Pls. 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1984">Serène, 1984</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, as having priority over 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC81FC91FB5CFC81" authority="Takeda &amp; Nagai, 1986" authorityName="Takeda &amp; Nagai" authorityYear="1986" box="[867,1276,802,825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC81FC91FBA4FC81" box="[867,1028,802,825]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporoides</emphasis>
Takeda &amp; Nagai, 1986
</taxonomicName>
. Davie &amp; Turner (1994) described a fourth species, 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFB4BFCF1FAA7FCE1" authorityName="Davie &amp; Turner" authorityYear="1994" box="[1193,1287,834,857]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asper">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFB4BFCF1FAA7FCE1" box="[1193,1287,834,857]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">H. asper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from Western Australia. 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFC7EFCD1FB87FCC1" authorityName="Serene" authorityYear="1984" box="[924,1063,866,889]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFC7EFCD1FB87FCC1" box="[924,1063,866,889]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Hepatoporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
now contains five species, including 
<taxonomicName id="41BFEDBBFF8DFF8AFCCCFC31FC36FC21" authority="Mendoza &amp; Ng, 2008" authorityName="Mendoza &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2008" box="[814,918,898,921]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumex" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B4CB4A2AFF8DFF8AFCCCFC31FC36FC21" box="[814,918,898,921]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">H. pumex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="AFF8F751FF8DFF8AFC46FC31FB88FC21" box="[932,1064,898,921]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
